But we may go a step further yet. The first of the two charters dates itself, as we have seen, subse- quently to 1131, perhaps even after 11333 but the second, as addressed to Archbishop Thurstan and Bishop Geofl'rey of Durham, who were contemporaries in their several dignities only from 1133 to 1 140, must take date within that interval of six or seven years, and probably towards the latter limit of it.
